    73â†’## Installation
    74â†’
    75â†’```sh
    76â†’> npm install neverthrow
    77â†’```
    79â†’## Recommended: Use `eslint-plugin-neverthrow`
    80â†’
    81â†’As part of `neverthrow`s [bounty program](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/issues/314), user [mdbetancourt](https://github.com/mdbetancourt) created [`eslint-plugin-neverthrow`](https://github.com/mdbetancourt/eslint-plugin-neverthrow) to ensure that errors are not gone unhandled.
   100â†’## Top-Level API
   101â†’
   102â†’`neverthrow` exposes the following:
   139â†’## API Documentation
   140â†’
   141â†’### Synchronous API (`Result`)
   142â†’
   143â†’#### `ok`
   144â†’
   145â†’Constructs an `Ok` variant of `Result`
   168â†’#### `err`
   169â†’
   170â†’Constructs an `Err` variant of `Result`
   193â†’#### `Result.isOk` (method)
   194â†’
   195â†’Returns `true` if the result is an `Ok` variant
   207â†’#### `Result.isErr` (method)
   208â†’
   209â†’Returns `true` if the result is an `Err` variant
   221â†’#### `Result.map` (method)
   222â†’
   223â†’Maps a `Result<T, E>` to `Result<U, E>` by applying a function to a contained `Ok` value, leaving an `Err` value untouched.
   259â†’#### `Result.mapErr` (method)
   260â†’
   261â†’Maps a `Result<T, E>` to `Result<T, F>` by applying a function to a contained `Err` value, leaving an `Ok` value untouched.
   297â†’#### `Result.unwrapOr` (method)
   298â†’
   299â†’Unwrap the `Ok` value, or return the default if there is an `Err`
   323â†’#### `Result.andThen` (method)
   324â†’
   325â†’Same idea as `map` above. Except you must return a new `Result`.
   384â†’#### `Result.asyncAndThen` (method)
   385â†’
   386â†’Same idea as [`andThen` above](#resultandthen-method), except you must return a new `ResultAsync`.
   404â†’#### `Result.orElse` (method)
   405â†’
   406â†’Takes an `Err` value and maps it to a `Result<T, SomeNewType>`. This is useful for error recovery.
   445â†’#### `Result.match` (method)
   446â†’
   447â†’Given 2 functions (one for the `Ok` variant and one for the `Err` variant) execute the function that matches the `Result` variant.
   514â†’#### `Result.asyncMap` (method)
   515â†’
   516â†’Similar to `map` except for two things:
   551â†’#### `Result.andTee` (method)
   552â†’
   553â†’Takes a `Result<T, E>` and lets the original `Result<T, E>` pass through regardless the result of the passed-in function.
   554â†’This is a handy way to handle side effects whose failure or success should not affect your main logics such as logging. 
   598â†’#### `Result.orTee` (method)
   599â†’
   600â†’Like `andTee` for the error track. Takes a `Result<T, E>` and lets the `Err` value pass through regardless the result of the passed-in function.
   601â†’This is a handy way to handle side effects whose failure or success should not affect your main logics such as logging.
   645â†’#### `Result.andThrough` (method)
   646â†’
   647â†’Similar to `andTee` except for:
   692â†’#### `Result.asyncAndThrough` (method)
   693â†’
   694â†’Similar to `andThrough` except you must return a ResultAsync. 
   728â†’#### `Result.fromThrowable` (static class method)
   729â†’
   730â†’> Although Result is not an actual JS class, the way that `fromThrowable` has been implemented requires that you call `fromThrowable` as though it were a static method on `Result`. See examples below.
   761â†’#### `Result.combine` (static class method)
   762â†’
   763â†’> Although Result is not an actual JS class, the way that `combine` has been implemented requires that you call `combine` as though it were a static method on `Result`. See examples below.
   814â†’#### `Result.combineWithAllErrors` (static class method)
   815â†’
   816â†’> Although Result is not an actual JS class, the way that `combineWithAllErrors` has been implemented requires that you call `combineWithAllErrors` as though it were a static method on `Result`. See examples below.
   852â†’#### `Result.safeUnwrap()`
   853â†’
   854â†’**Deprecated**. You don't need to use this method anymore.
   863â†’### Asynchronous API (`ResultAsync`)
   864â†’
   865â†’#### `okAsync`
   866â†’
   867â†’Constructs an `Ok` variant of `ResultAsync`
   892â†’#### `errAsync`
   893â†’
   894â†’Constructs an `Err` variant of `ResultAsync`
   919â†’#### `ResultAsync.fromThrowable` (static class method)
   920â†’
   921â†’Similar to [Result.fromThrowable](#resultfromthrowable-static-class-method), but for functions that return a `Promise`.
   960â†’#### `ResultAsync.fromPromise` (static class method)
   961â†’
   962â†’Transforms a `PromiseLike<T>` (that may throw) into a `ResultAsync<T, E>`.
   996â†’#### `ResultAsync.fromSafePromise` (static class method)
   997â†’
   998â†’Same as `ResultAsync.fromPromise` except that it does not handle the rejection of the promise. **Ensure you know what you're doing, otherwise a thrown exception within this promise will cause ResultAsync to reject, instead of resolve to a Result.**
  1041â†’#### `ResultAsync.map` (method)
  1042â†’
  1043â†’Maps a `ResultAsync<T, E>` to `ResultAsync<U, E>` by applying a function to a contained `Ok` value, leaving an `Err` value untouched.
  1087â†’#### `ResultAsync.mapErr` (method)
  1088â†’
  1089â†’Maps a `ResultAsync<T, E>` to `ResultAsync<T, F>` by applying a function to a contained `Err` value, leaving an `Ok` value untouched.
  1142â†’#### `ResultAsync.unwrapOr` (method)
  1143â†’
  1144â†’Unwrap the `Ok` value, or return the default if there is an `Err`.  
  1145â†’Works just like `Result.unwrapOr` but returns a `Promise<T>` instead of `T`.
  1166â†’#### `ResultAsync.andThen` (method)
  1167â†’
  1168â†’Same idea as `map` above. Except the applied function must return a `Result` or `ResultAsync`.
  1223â†’#### `ResultAsync.orElse` (method)
  1224â†’
  1225â†’Takes an `Err` value and maps it to a `ResultAsync<T, SomeNewType>`. This is useful for error recovery.
  1241â†’#### `ResultAsync.match` (method)
  1242â†’
  1243â†’Given 2 functions (one for the `Ok` variant and one for the `Err` variant) execute the function that matches the `ResultAsync` variant.
  1283â†’#### `ResultAsync.andTee` (method)
  1284â†’
  1285â†’Takes a `ResultAsync<T, E>` and lets the original `ResultAsync<T, E>` pass through regardless 
  1286â†’the result of the passed-in function.
  1287â†’This is a handy way to handle side effects whose failure or success should not affect your main logics such as logging. 
  1330â†’#### `ResultAsync.orTee` (method)
  1331â†’
  1332â†’Like `andTee` for the error track. Takes a `ResultAsync<T, E>` and lets the original `Err` value pass through regardless 
  1333â†’the result of the passed-in function.
  1334â†’This is a handy way to handle side effects whose failure or success should not affect your main logics such as logging. 
  1377â†’#### `ResultAsync.andThrough` (method)
  1378â†’
  1379â†’
  1380â†’Similar to `andTee` except for:
  1425â†’#### `ResultAsync.combine` (static class method)
  1426â†’
  1427â†’Combine lists of `ResultAsync`s.
  1475â†’#### `ResultAsync.combineWithAllErrors` (static class method)
  1476â†’
  1477â†’Like `combine` but without short-circuiting. Instead of just the first error value, you get a list of all error values of the input result list.
  1509â†’#### `ResultAsync.safeUnwrap()`
  1510â†’
  1511â†’**Deprecated**. You don't need to use this method anymore.
  1519â†’### Utilities
  1520â†’
  1521â†’#### `fromThrowable`
  1522â†’
  1523â†’Top level export of `Result.fromThrowable`.
  1524â†’Please find documentation at [Result.fromThrowable](#resultfromthrowable-static-class-method)
  1528â†’#### `fromAsyncThrowable`
  1529â†’
  1530â†’Top level export of `ResultAsync.fromThrowable`.
  1531â†’Please find documentation at [ResultAsync.fromThrowable](#resultasyncfromthrowable-static-class-method)
  1535â†’#### `fromPromise`
  1536â†’
  1537â†’Top level export of `ResultAsync.fromPromise`.
  1538â†’Please find documentation at [ResultAsync.fromPromise](#resultasyncfrompromise-static-class-method)
  1542â†’#### `fromSafePromise`
  1543â†’
  1544â†’Top level export of `ResultAsync.fromSafePromise`.
  1545â†’Please find documentation at [ResultAsync.fromSafePromise](#resultasyncfromsafepromise-static-class-method)
  1549â†’#### `safeTry`
  1550â†’
  1551â†’Used to implicitly return errors and reduce boilerplate.
  1633â†’### Testing
  1634â†’
  1635â†’`Result` instances have two unsafe methods, aptly called `_unsafeUnwrap` and `_unsafeUnwrapErr` which **should only be used in a test environment**.
  1673â†’## A note on the Package Name
  1674â†’
  1675â†’Although the package is called `neverthrow`, please don't take this literally. I am simply encouraging the developer to think a bit more about the ergonomics and usage of whatever software they are writing.
  1681â†’### License
  1682â†’
  1683â†’The neverthrow project is available as open source under the terms of the [MIT license](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/blob/master/LICENSE).
